Echinochloa utilis

    Authority   Ohwi & Yabuno
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5603

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A tall, robust, vigorous grass up to 120 cm high.
   USES Very palatable and used for pasture. It can be grazed as early as
   three weeks after sowing when the grass is 30-40 cm tall and it can be
   grazed up to five times in a season. It makes good hay and silage. Also
   used for erosion control after timber clearing. GROWING PERIOD
   Summer-growing annual grass. Require 40 days for grass crop and 100
   days for grain crop. COMMON NAMES Shirohie millet, Japanese millet.
   FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: E. crus-galli var. frumentacea.
   Shirohie millet is widely cultivated in the tropics and subtropics. It
   is fairly drought tolerant but will not survive fire when dry enough to
   burn. Yields of up to 35 t/ha of green material can be obtained.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Skerman P 1990 pp 393-396 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, FER, LIG]
   Duke J 1979 pp 95 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]

